Surveillance video from the lobby of an Atlantic City casino released Friday shows what happened after disgraced NFL star Ray Rice knocked out his wife-to-be.

The footage from inside the now-defunct Revel Casino obtained exclusively by ABC News shows a distraught Janay Palmer, Rice's now-wife, refusing to talk to the Baltimore Ravens player after getting punched in the face inside the elevator moments earlier.

The woman is seen in the video pushing away the 5-foot-8, 206-pound athlete when he tries to come near her.

