The 45-minute never-before-seen tape, which has been edited down to just over 2 minutes by ABC, also shows how Janay Palmer's demeanor changes over time, going from furious to emotional, and ultimately to forgiving.

When Rice is escorted out of the hotel and casino in handcuffs, his fiancee is seen kissing and nuzzling him on the neck in an elevator. 

Rice and Palmer were each charged with assault, but the count against the woman was later dropped due to lack of sufficient evidence. 

The Ravens star was indicted on an an upgraded charge of aggravated assault, but instead of serving time he was allowed to enter a pretrial prevention program, which would allow his criminal record to be expunged.

